<chapter>
<title>Gentoo International</title>

<section>
<title>Russia: Gentoo meeting, Moscow</title>
<body>

<p>
On Saturday, 23 December 2006, there was a meeting of Russian members of the
Gentoo community. Currently, the Russian Gentoo community is split into two
independent groups: the Russian translators team and the team that supports
the Russian Gentoo forums and other gentoo community resources. Both of these
teams put effort into translation of the GWN and other documentation. It's
clear that consolidation of efforts is beneficial for both of the teams and for
the users. This decision was made between Peter Volkov from the Russian
translation team and Anton Chaplygin and Anton Senkovsky from the forums team.
</p>

<p>
Another part of meeting was devoted to playing with exciting beryl desktop
effects, solving logical problems, beer and fun. Photos are available on
<uri link="ftp://gentoo.ru/pub/GentooMetting4Photos/">gentoo.ru</uri>.
</p>

</body>
